    <h1 class="mb-6">SearchGPT Optimisation</h1>

    <img src="/images/content/five-signal-model.svg" alt="The Five Signal Model for AI search" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">SearchGPT is OpenAI's dedicated search product – a real-time web search feature integrated into ChatGPT. Unlike standard ChatGPT which draws from training data, SearchGPT actively crawls the web to provide current answers.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">SearchGPT uses Bing as its primary data source. The top ranking factors are: link quality, relevance, freshness, link quantity, and content depth. This creates new opportunities for businesses to gain visibility in AI-powered search results.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Our analysis of 1,400+ UK businesses shows that companies with strong Bing visibility are 3x more likely to appear in SearchGPT results. The businesses performing best have consistent entity signals across multiple platforms.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">How SearchGPT Differs from Standard ChatGPT</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Standard ChatGPT responses draw from training data – what the model learned during training. SearchGPT adds real-time web retrieval on top of this. If your business is well-represented in Bing's index AND has strong entity signals in the training data, you get recommended in both modes.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The key difference lies in timing and data sources. Standard ChatGPT has a knowledge cutoff date. SearchGPT can access information published minutes ago. This means recent news, product launches, or business updates can influence SearchGPT responses immediately.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">SearchGPT also provides source citations. Users can see where information comes from and visit the original websites. This creates a direct pathway from AI responses to your business website – something standard ChatGPT cannot offer.</p>

<h3>Response Speed and Accuracy</h3>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">SearchGPT responses take longer to generate because they involve real-time web crawling. However, the accuracy improves significantly for time-sensitive queries. Business hours, pricing, availability, and current events receive more accurate responses.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">For example, if someone asks "What are the opening hours for Italian restaurants in Manchester today?", SearchGPT can check current websites for holiday schedules or temporary closures. Standard ChatGPT would rely on older training data.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">SearchGPT's Technical Architecture</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">SearchGPT combines OpenAI's language model with Bing's search infrastructure. When you submit a query, the system first determines if real-time data would improve the response. If yes, it searches Bing's index for relevant, current information.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The system then synthesises web results with the language model's existing knowledge. This hybrid approach allows for more comprehensive and current responses than either system could provide alone.</p>

<h3>Data Integration Process</h3>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The integration happens in three stages. First, SearchGPT analyses your query for real-time information needs. Second, it searches Bing for relevant current data. Third, it combines web results with pre-trained knowledge to generate a response.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">This process explains why some queries trigger SearchGPT while others use standard responses. Business-related queries, current events, and factual lookups typically activate the search component.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Key Ranking Factors for SearchGPT</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">SearchGPT inherits many ranking signals from Bing. However, our research with UK businesses reveals some unique patterns. Content depth matters more than traditional SEO factors like keyword density.</p>

